Step 1: Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio.
• From the balance sheet, the Total Liabilities are given by the “Total Current Liabilities” (since no other liabilities are listed), which is 3,376,304.04.
• The Total Assets at the end date are 19,520,226.07.
• Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets = 3,376,304.04 / 19,520,226.07 ≈ 0.1729, which rounds to 0.17.

Step 2: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio.
• From the cash flow statement, the Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities is given as –4,510,837.08.
• From the income statement, the Net Profit is 143,922.03.
• Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = Operating CF / Net Profit = (–4,510,837.08) / 143,922.03 ≈ –31.33.

Thus, the final answer is:
